events.description: The Roman legions on the Rhine refuse to declare their allegiance to Galba, instead proclaiming their legate, Aulus Vitellius, as emperor.
events.html: • 69 – The Roman legions on the Rhine refuse to declare their allegiance to Galba, instead proclaiming their legate, Aulus Vitellius, as emperor.[1]

events.description: Emperor Decius orders everyone in the Roman Empire (except Jews) to make sacrifices to the Roman gods.
events.html: • 250 – Emperor Decius orders everyone in the Roman Empire (except Jews) to make sacrifices to the Roman gods.[2]

events.description: Pope Leo X excommunicates Martin Luther in the papal bull Decet Romanum Pontificem.
events.html: • 1521 – Pope Leo X excommunicates Martin Luther in the papal bull Decet Romanum Pontificem.[3]

events.description: By the Coonan Cross Oath, the Eastern Church in India cuts itself off from colonial Portuguese tutelage.
events.html: • 1653 – By the Coonan Cross Oath, the Eastern Church in India cuts itself off from colonial Portuguese tutelage.[4]

events.description: Benning Wentworth issues the first of the New Hampshire Grants, leading to the establishment of Vermont.
events.html: • 1749 – Benning Wentworth issues the first of the New Hampshire Grants, leading to the establishment of Vermont.[5]

events.description: The first issue of Berlingske, Denmark's oldest continually operating newspaper, is published.
events.html: • 1749 – The first issue of Berlingske, Denmark's oldest continually operating newspaper, is published.[6]

events.description: American Revolutionary War: American forces under General George Washington defeat British forces at the Battle of Princeton, helping boost patriot morale.
events.html: • 1777 – American Revolutionary War: American forces under General George Washington defeat British forces at the Battle of Princeton, helping boost patriot morale.[7]

events.description: Austria, the United Kingdom, and France form a secret defensive alliance against Prussia and Russia.
events.html: • 1815 – Austria, the United Kingdom, and France form a secret defensive alliance against Prussia and Russia.[8]

events.description: Captain James Onslow, in the Clio, reasserts British sovereignty over the Falkland Islands.
events.html: • 1833 – Captain James Onslow, in the Clio, reasserts British sovereignty over the Falkland Islands.[9]

entities.name: Reassertion of British sovereignty over the Falkland Islands (1833)

events.description: Joseph Jenkins Roberts is sworn in as the first president of Liberia.
events.html: • 1848 – Joseph Jenkins Roberts is sworn in as the first president of Liberia.[10]

events.description: American Civil War: Delaware votes not to secede from the United States.
events.html: • 1861 – American Civil War: Delaware votes not to secede from the United States.[11]

events.description: Meiji Restoration in Japan: The Tokugawa shogunate is abolished; agents of Satsuma and Chōshū seize power.
events.html: • 1868 – Meiji Restoration in Japan: The Tokugawa shogunate is abolished; agents of Satsuma and Chōshū seize power.[12]

events.description: Construction work begins on the Brooklyn Bridge in New York, United States.
events.html: • 1870 – Construction work begins on the Brooklyn Bridge in New York, United States.[13]

events.description: In the Battle of Bapaume, an engagement in the Franco-Prussian War, General Louis Faidherbe's forces bring about a Prussian retreat.
events.html: • 1871 – In the Battle of Bapaume, an engagement in the Franco-Prussian War, General Louis Faidherbe's forces bring about a Prussian retreat.[14]

events.description: Sino-French War: Beginning of the Battle of Núi Bop.
events.html: • 1885 – Sino-French War: Beginning of the Battle of Núi Bop.[15]

events.description: A magnitude 7.7 earthquake destroys the city of Almaty in Russian Turkestan.
events.html: • 1911 – A magnitude 7.7 earthquake destroys the city of Almaty in Russian Turkestan.[16]

events.description: A gun battle in the East End of London leaves two dead. It sparked a political row over the involvement of then-Home Secretary Winston Churchill.
events.html: • 1911 – A gun battle in the East End of London leaves two dead. It sparked a political row over the involvement of then-Home Secretary Winston Churchill.[17]

events.description: An Atlantic coast storm sets the lowest confirmed barometric pressure reading (955.0 mb (28.20 inHg)) for a non-tropical system in the continental United States.
events.html: • 1913 – An Atlantic coast storm sets the lowest confirmed barometric pressure reading (955.0 mb (28.20 inHg)) for a non-tropical system in the continental United States.[18]

events.description: First Balkan War: Greece completes its capture of the eastern Aegean island of Chios, as the last Ottoman forces on the island surrender.
events.html: • 1913 – First Balkan War: Greece completes its capture of the eastern Aegean island of Chios, as the last Ottoman forces on the island surrender.[19][20]

events.description: Over 640 are killed after a magnitude 6.4 earthquake strikes the Mexican states Puebla and Veracruz.
events.html: • 1920 – Over 640 are killed after a magnitude 6.4 earthquake strikes the Mexican states Puebla and Veracruz.[21]

events.description: Minnie D. Craig becomes the first woman elected as Speaker of the North Dakota House of Representatives, the first woman to hold a Speaker position anywhere in the United States.
events.html: • 1933 – Minnie D. Craig becomes the first woman elected as Speaker of the North Dakota House of Representatives, the first woman to hold a Speaker position anywhere in the United States.[22]

entities.name: Speaker of the North Dakota House of Representatives

events.description: World War II: US flying ace Major Greg "Pappy" Boyington is shot down in his Vought F4U Corsair by Captain Masajiro Kawato flying a Mitsubishi A6M Zero.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: US flying ace Major Greg "Pappy" Boyington is shot down in his Vought F4U Corsair by Captain Masajiro Kawato flying a Mitsubishi A6M Zero.[23]

entities.name: List of World War II aces from Japan

events.description: Popular Canadian American jockey George Woolf suffers a concussion during a freak racing accident; he dies from the injury the following day. The annual George Woolf Memorial Jockey Award is created to honor him.
events.html: • 1946 – Popular Canadian American jockey George Woolf suffers a concussion during a freak racing accident; he dies from the injury the following day. The annual George Woolf Memorial Jockey Award is created to honor him.[24]

events.description: Proceedings of the U.S. Congress are televised for the first time.
events.html: • 1947 – Proceedings of the U.S. Congress are televised for the first time.[25]

events.description: The Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas, the central bank of the Philippines, is established.
events.html: • 1949 – The Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas, the central bank of the Philippines, is established.[26]

events.description: Frances P. Bolton and her son, Oliver from Ohio, become the first mother and son to serve simultaneously in the U.S. Congress.
events.html: • 1953 – Frances P. Bolton and her son, Oliver from Ohio, become the first mother and son to serve simultaneously in the U.S. Congress.[27]

events.description: A fire damages the top part of the Eiffel Tower.
events.html: • 1956 – A fire damages the top part of the Eiffel Tower.[28]

events.description: The Hamilton Watch Company introduces the first electric watch.
events.html: • 1957 – The Hamilton Watch Company introduces the first electric watch.[29]

events.description: The West Indies Federation is formed.
events.html: • 1958 – The West Indies Federation is formed.[30]

events.description: Alaska is admitted as the 49th U.S. state.
events.html: • 1959 – Alaska is admitted as the 49th U.S. state.[31]

events.description: Cold War: After a series of economic retaliations against one another, the United States severs diplomatic relations with Cuba.
events.html: • 1961 – Cold War: After a series of economic retaliations against one another, the United States severs diplomatic relations with Cuba.[32]

events.description: The SL-1 nuclear reactor, near Idaho Falls, Idaho, is destroyed by a steam explosion in the only reactor incident in the United States to cause immediate fatalities.
events.html: • 1961 – The SL-1 nuclear reactor, near Idaho Falls, Idaho, is destroyed by a steam explosion in the only reactor incident in the United States to cause immediate fatalities.[33]

events.description: A protest by agricultural workers in Baixa de Cassanje, Portuguese Angola, turns into a revolt, opening the Angolan War of Independence, the first of the Portuguese Colonial Wars.
events.html: • 1961 – A protest by agricultural workers in Baixa de Cassanje, Portuguese Angola, turns into a revolt, opening the Angolan War of Independence, the first of the Portuguese Colonial Wars.[34]

events.description: Aero Flight 311 crashes into the forest in Kvevlax, Finland, killing 25 people.
events.html: • 1961 – Aero Flight 311 crashes into the forest in Kvevlax, Finland, killing 25 people.[35]

events.description: Pope John XXIII excommunicates Fidel Castro.
events.html: • 1962 – Pope John XXIII excommunicates Fidel Castro.[36]

events.description: The International Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights, adopted by the United Nations General Assembly, comes into force.
events.html: • 1976 – The International Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights, adopted by the United Nations General Assembly, comes into force.[37]

entities.name: International Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights

events.description: Apple Computer is incorporated.
events.html: • 1977 – Apple Computer is incorporated.[38]

events.description: Varig Flight 797 crashes near Akouré in the Ivory Coast, resulting in 50 deaths.
events.html: • 1987 – Varig Flight 797 crashes near Akouré in the Ivory Coast, resulting in 50 deaths.[39]

events.description: United States invasion of Panama: Manuel Noriega, former leader of Panama, surrenders to American forces.
events.html: • 1990 – United States invasion of Panama: Manuel Noriega, former leader of Panama, surrenders to American forces.[40]

events.description: CommutAir Flight 4821 crashes on approach to Adirondack Regional Airport, in Saranac Lake, New York, killing two people.
events.html: • 1992 – CommutAir Flight 4821 crashes on approach to Adirondack Regional Airport, in Saranac Lake, New York, killing two people.[41]

events.description: In Moscow, Russia, George H. W. Bush and Boris Yeltsin sign the second Strategic Arms Reduction Treaty (START).
events.html: • 1993 – In Moscow, Russia, George H. W. Bush and Boris Yeltsin sign the second Strategic Arms Reduction Treaty (START).[42]

events.description: Baikal Airlines Flight 130 crashes near Mamoney, Irkutsk, Russia, resulting in 125 deaths.
events.html: • 1994 – Baikal Airlines Flight 130 crashes near Mamoney, Irkutsk, Russia, resulting in 125 deaths.[43]

events.description: The Mars Polar Lander is launched by NASA.
events.html: • 1999 – The Mars Polar Lander is launched by NASA.[44]

events.description: Israeli–Palestinian conflict: Israeli forces seize the Palestinian freighter Karine A in the Red Sea, finding 50 tons of weapons.
events.html: • 2002 – Israeli–Palestinian conflict: Israeli forces seize the Palestinian freighter Karine A in the Red Sea, finding 50 tons of weapons.[45]

events.description: Flash Airlines Flight 604 crashes into the Red Sea, resulting in 148 deaths, making it one of the deadliest aviation accidents in Egyptian history.
events.html: • 2004 – Flash Airlines Flight 604 crashes into the Red Sea, resulting in 148 deaths, making it one of the deadliest aviation accidents in Egyptian history.[46]

events.description: The first block of the blockchain of the decentralized payment system Bitcoin, called the Genesis block, is established by the creator of the system, Satoshi Nakamoto.
events.html: • 2009 – The first block of the blockchain of the decentralized payment system Bitcoin, called the Genesis block, is established by the creator of the system, Satoshi Nakamoto.[47]

events.description: Boko Haram militants destroy the entire town of Baga in north-east Nigeria, starting the Baga massacre and killing as many as 2,000 people.
events.html: • 2015 – Boko Haram militants destroy the entire town of Baga in north-east Nigeria, starting the Baga massacre and killing as many as 2,000 people.[48]

events.description: In response to the execution of Nimr al-Nimr, Iran ends its diplomatic relations with Saudi Arabia.
events.html: • 2016 – In response to the execution of Nimr al-Nimr, Iran ends its diplomatic relations with Saudi Arabia.[49]

events.description: For the first time in history, all five major storm surge gates in the Netherlands are closed simultaneously in the wake of a storm.
events.html: • 2018 – For the first time in history, all five major storm surge gates in the Netherlands are closed simultaneously in the wake of a storm.[50]

events.description: Chang'e 4 makes the first soft landing on the far side of the Moon, deploying the Yutu-2 lunar rover.
events.html: • 2019 – Chang'e 4 makes the first soft landing on the far side of the Moon, deploying the Yutu-2 lunar rover.[51]

events.description: Iranian General Qasem Soleimani is killed by an American airstrike near Baghdad International Airport, igniting global concerns of a potential armed conflict.
events.html: • 2020 – Iranian General Qasem Soleimani is killed by an American airstrike near Baghdad International Airport, igniting global concerns of a potential armed conflict.[52]

events.description: Singapore's Jurong Bird Park permanently closes.
events.html: • 2023 – Singapore's Jurong Bird Park permanently closes.[53]

events.description: At least 91 people are killed in bombings in Kerman, Iran, during a ceremony commemorating the assassination of Iranian General Qasem Soleimani 4 years ago.
events.html: • 2024 – At least 91 people are killed in bombings in Kerman, Iran, during a ceremony commemorating the assassination of Iranian General Qasem Soleimani 4 years ago.[54]
